SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 33-7-301, is amended by deleting
subsection (d) and substituting:
(d)
(1) If a defendant is found to be incompetent to stand trial, any
misdemeanor charges pending at the time of the incompetency determination
must be retired no later than two (2) years after the date of arrest when the
misdemeanor charge or charges have not otherwise been disposed of except
that misdemeanor charges must not be retired pursuant to this subdivision (d)(1)
if the defendant is restored to competency prior to the date on which the
misdemeanor charge or charges would have otherwise been retired under this
subdivision (d)(1).
(2) When a defendant whose charges were retired in accordance with
subdivision (d)(1) is released into the community, the chief officer shall:
(A) Notify the court of the defendant's discharge; and
(B) Provide the court and the sheriff with an outpatient treatment
plan that accounts for the safety of the community.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 33-7-301(c), is amended by deleting
the last sentence and substituting:
